{
    "title": "Kettlebell Lateral Raise",
    "description": "A strength exercise.",
    "difficulty": "Beginner",
    "content": [
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "Instructions",
            "content": {
                "type": "steps",
                "items": [
                    "Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a kettlebell in your right hand.",
                    "Keep your arm straight and lift the kettlebell out to the side until it reaches shoulder height.",
                    "Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the kettlebell back down to your side.",
                    "Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to your left arm and repeat the exercise."
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "Benefits",
            "content": {
                "type": "list",
                "items": [
                    "Targets the lateral deltoid muscles, which are responsible for shoulder abduction and stabilization",
                    "Improves shoulder strength and stability",
                    "Helps to prevent shoulder injuries",
                    "Engages the core muscles for added stability and balance",
                    "Can be modified for different fitness levels and goals",
                    "Provides a full-body workout, as it also engages the legs and glutes for balance and stability"
                ]
            }
        },
